# Example only. Copy and adapt outside the repository before installing.
# Do NOT embed GitHub tokens, SSH keys, opencode API keys, or other secrets
# here. API credentials must be provided via the environment (gh auth and
# opencode auth), not committed files.
#
# Cautious real opencode scheduled profile (Level 10H).
#
# What this profile does:
# - Execution-only. Each tick runs at most one eligible GitHub Issue / one
#   local task through the one-shot pipeline to waiting_approval, then stops.
# - One issue / one task per tick. This is not a daemon, scheduler loop,
#   webhook, background worker, or multi-task batch.
# - Shared lock protection. The scheduler tick shares the non-overlap lock
#   with manual write-capable runs, so concurrent ticks cannot overlap. A
#   contended tick returns a safe no-op result and stops.
# - Observability summary. The example passes
#   `--include-observability-summary`, so each JSONL tick line additionally
#   carries a top-level `observability_summary` (the read-only
#   UnifiedExecutionSummary). The real scheduled dashboard reads it when
#   present; older log lines without it still work through the legacy
#   fallback. This is additive observability output only and does not change
#   scheduler execution semantics.
#
# What this profile does NOT do:
# - No publish, no draft PR, no branch push, no PR merge, no approval, and no
#   teardown of branches or worktrees. Human review remains the final gate.
#
# How to disable:
# - Comment out (prefix with `#`) or remove the crontab line below using
#   `crontab -e`.
#
# Schedule:
# - Runs every 30 minutes by default. Adjust the schedule only after observing
#   stable execution-only ticks for at least 24 hours.

*/30 * * * * cd /home/ubuntu/agent-taskflow && { [ -f .venv/bin/activate ] && . .venv/bin/activate; }; python scripts/run_github_issue_one_task_scheduler_tick.py --repo anderson930420/agent-taskflow --db-path "$HOME/.agent-taskflow/state.db" --local-repo-path /home/ubuntu/agent-taskflow --artifact-root /home/ubuntu/agent-taskflow/artifacts/scheduler-tick --worktree-root /home/ubuntu/agent-taskflow/.worktrees --issue-limit 20 --operator cron-confirmed-real --operator-note "cron confirmed real opencode execution-only tick" --confirmed --executor opencode --model "minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7" --validator policy --include-observability-summary --json >> /home/ubuntu/agent-taskflow/logs/github-issue-one-task-real-opencode.jsonl 2>&1
